    jobDescription:
      "<p> </p><p>The Role</p><p>As a member of our product engineering team, you'll be responsible for sustaining (and raising!) the bar for user-friendly, and delightful UX. You'll work closely with our cross-functional product team to conceptualize, implement, and ship features from start to finish. You'll be a technical leader on the frontend, building reusable components and defining new UI patterns, so our platform scales smoothly as our product grows.</p><p>Most of our eng team works remotely from Japan and India. We're big believers in trust and in a healthy work/life balance: we want you to be productive and connected with the team.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Product development:</strong> Work closely with the engineering and product team to plan, architect, and implement features across our core product. You'll partner especially closely with the design, backend team and executing on an aligned vision.</li><li><strong>Technical leadership:</strong> Employ software engineering best practices to ensure that our code-base remains well-tested and bug-free. As a lead engineer, youll have a prominent voice in engineering decisions and technical direction.</li><li><strong>Customer satisfaction:</strong> Ensure that our customers are successful, happy, and engaged. You'll work to understand their workflows and pain points, and always be looking for opportunities to improve their experience and make their jobs easier.</li></ul><p><strong>What We're Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Experience:</strong> 5+ years of professional software experience, including meaningful experience in front-end web development. You've built complex user interfaces, worked with internal APIs, and shipped to real customers on a regular basis.</li><li><strong>Browser:</strong> Solid understanding of JavaScript, DOM, web components, and CSS. You've used Vue, or a Vue-like UI framework, and know your way around CSS concepts like flex-box.</li><li><strong>Product focused:</strong> You take pride in building elegant, beautiful, and user-friendly products.</li><li><strong>Problem solver:</strong> You're good at understanding and breaking down complex problems. You are resourceful and comfortable with ambiguity, and can make good decisions and forward progress even when requirements are unclear.</li><li><strong>Great communicator:</strong> You engage thoughtfully and effectively with others, and you're an attentive and empathetic listener. You can adapt your communication style to different audiences and confidently break down tricky topics in writing and in person.</li><li><strong>Growth mindset:</strong> You're eager to learn, comfortable asking questions, and receptive to feedback.</li></ul><p>Bonus Points</p><ul><li><strong>Modern tech:</strong> Familiarity working with Vue, TypeScript.</li><li><strong>Startup:</strong> You've worked in a fast-paced startup environment in the past and are excited to do it again.</li><li><strong>Track record:</strong> You have a proven history of teamwork, initiative, and grit; regardless of profession or position.</li></ul><p>Our Stack at ThreeSides</p><p>We work mostly in Ruby and Typescript. However, languages can be learned. What is important to us is that you have strong software engineering fundamentals, rather than your knowledge of particular frameworks or languages.</p><ul><li>Framework: NuxtJS with Typescript(Frontend) & Ruby on Rails(Backend)</li><li>Persistence: Postgres</li><li>Architecture: RESTful client server architecture</li><li>Infrastructure: We're hosted on AWS, and make extensive use of, amongst others, SES, S3, ECS, RDS, CloudFront and CloudWatch</li><li>Processes: We believe continuous delivery is essential for moving safely at speed, so we deploy all changes to production automatically after running extensive automated tests</li></ul>",
